title: Grateful Dead Live at Mickey's ranch studio on 1982-01-01

reviews.review_text: This recording bugs me A lame and tedious attempt at humor.  Sounds like a bunch of rich high school kids.  Leave the musical humor to Zappa, boys.

I Thought It Was Funny This is a cute bit of radio-play similar to War of the Worlds. Just don't expect studio jams and banter (although there are nice sound fx and musical interludes including a clip from "Deep, Wide and Frequent"). I never knew about this until the other day and it does add another piece to the puzzle of what these guys think, for what that's worth :)
?? does anyone have more info on this??

Nah.. Made me laugh at times, but over all I found it annoying... awful story..

None the less, it is high quality.  Download becuase it is rare.

This deserves your attention This radio play has many creepy echoes of today's public discourse.  It is not just a comedy.  It deserves your attention.

Also, it reminds the listener of our place in the ecosystem relative to bugs, which is important to bear in mind.
Testing Testing One Two three Four.  Testing Testing.
